name: Man City vs Real Madrid
summary: Manchester City's reign as Champions League holders ended dramatically on Wednesday as Real Madrid prevailed 4-3 on penalties following a thrilling 4-4 draw at the Santiago Bernabéu. In a pulsating encounter, Real Madrid overturned a two-goal deficit to force extra time, before ultimately securing their place in the semi-finals. The result was hailed as a "lesson" in Champions League football by ESPN, with Real Madrid's experienced and resilient team outplaying the youthful exuberance of Manchester City. Despite the disappointment, Manchester City manager Pep Guardiola expressed no regrets, acknowledging the quality of Real Madrid's performance. Both Yahoo Sports and The Athletic provide in-depth analysis of the match, while CBS Sports and CNET offer practical information on how to watch the game live online. NBC Sports, Al Jazeera English, Business Insider, and Eurosport COM also cover the match, with a focus on the dramatic penalty shootout that ultimately decided the tie in favor of Real Madrid.

name: Jontay Porter
summary: Jontay Porter, a player for the Toronto Raptors, has been banned from the NBA for life for violating the league's gambling rules. This is the first gambling ban for a player in the NBA in 70 years. Investigations revealed that Porter bet on games, gave information to bettors, and limited his playing time for betting purposes. Specifically, Porter bet on the Raptors to lose a game. The league's decision is a result of a lengthy probe and is intended to deter any future gambling violations within the NBA.

summary: "Under the Bridge," a Hulu true-crime drama, follows the tragic murder of Reena Virk by a group of teens. Lily Gladstone and Riley Keough deliver powerful performances, bringing depth and nuance to their characters. Despite its familiar true-crime format, the show transcends the genre by exploring the complexities of the case and the lasting consequences for the victims and perpetrators involved. The series has received critical acclaim, with reviewers praising Gladstone and Keough's performances and the show's handling of the sensitive subject matter.

name: Mayorkas
summary: The House of Representatives has impeached Department of Homeland Security Secretary Alejandro Mayorkas, sending the articles of impeachment to the Senate for trial. The charges stem from allegations of mismanagement and dereliction of duty at the Department of Homeland Security. The Senate has voted to dismiss the articles without a trial, effectively acquitting Mayorkas. The impeachment process, which is highly unusual for a cabinet secretary, has sparked controversy and partisan debate. Some Republicans have supported the impeachment, while Democrats have largely opposed it. The Senate's decision to dismiss the charges without a trial has drawn criticism from some Republicans, who have argued that a full trial should have been held.

name: Michael J. Fox
summary: Michael J. Fox has been making waves with his recent comments on the evolution of fame. In an interview with PEOPLE, Fox recalled a humorous anecdote from the Back to the Future premiere, where he was close to approaching Princess Diana. Fox also received accolades from Ryan Reynolds, who recognized his contributions to Parkinson's disease awareness. Fox expressed his belief that fame in the 1980s was more demanding, requiring talent and dedication. He contrasted this with the ease of becoming famous today, suggesting that fame can be achieved through viral dance steps rather than genuine talent. Fox is open to the possibility of returning to acting and praised Taylor Swift as an exceptional artist who has a positive impact on the world.
